news.title: Chandigarh administration & Panjab University owe Rs 67 crore in property tax
news.para: ​​While the amount may decrease after reconciliation, as per the record of the civic body authority, the UT engineering department has to pay around Rs 45 crore while PU has to deposit Rs 22 crore for property tax or service charges.

news.title: Pune: Three years' extension for Panshet flood-affected societies to claim home ownership
news.para: The families badly affected due to 1961 Panshet flood are living on land given to them on lease by the state government. The government took a decision in March 2019 to transfer the ownership of the land to 103 co-operative societies.

news.title: Chhattisgarh agrees to demand of residential land distribution
news.para: The state government is ready to resolve the objections and Nava Raipur Atal Nagar Development Authority (NRAND) will start the process of distribution of 1200 to 2500 square feet residential land lease to the project affected-farmers as per their eligibility from March 7.

news.title: About 32% buildings in Ahmedabad don't have BU nod
news.para: In the overall survey, there were 55% hospitals without BU across zones; similarly, there were 42% educational buildings, 35% commercial units, 31% buildings that were of mixed-use, 12% among highrise residential buildings and 24% among lowrise buildings.

news.title: Direct Telangana to implement RERA provisions: Petitioner to HC
news.para: The bench gave notices to the state and its principal secretary, municipal administration, asking them to file their counters within four weeks.

news.title: Punjab to focus on green residences
news.para: As energy conservation building code for apartments is voluntary at present, it would soon be made mandatory for bigger dwelling units, including the multi-storeyed projects.

news.title: Manesar: Vatika Seven Lamps fined for releasing sewage into vacant plots
news.para: Residents of the society have complained that the sewage treatment plant (STP) set up at the society isn’t functioning properly.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC told to pay six-month rent to Green View EWS families
news.para: ​On Thursday, district town planner RS Batth shot a strongly worded letter to NBCC, directing it to provide immediate relief as agreed with the district administration.

news.title: Adani Properties leads race to buy HDIL
news.para: The other applicants include Sharda Constructions & Corporation Ltd, B-Right Real Estate Ltd, Urban Affordable Housing LLP, Toscano Infrastructure Pvt Ltd and Dev Land and Housing Ltd, the people said.

news.title: Macrotech set to repay $170 million offshore bonds next week, a year ahead of maturity
news.para: These bonds are part of a total $225 million debt raised by the developer’s wholly-owned subsidiary Lodha Developers International Ltd, Mauritius against its luxury residential projects in London.

news.title: MIDC set to allot 235 plots to industries at Ajang in Malegaon
news.para: According to MIDC officials, it may fetch around Rs 1,000 crore investment once these plots are sold and industries start the process to set up the plants there in the next two years, generating employment to over 5,000 people at least.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body to scrutinise waste treatment units installed in residential projects
news.para: The Kolhapur Municipal Corporation (KMC) is going to audit the status of the waste water treatment plants installed in the residential buildings.

news.title: Delhi: On-demand construction & demolition waste collection yet to take off fully
news.para: The east and south corporations started the facility in December 2021 and February 2022, respectively, to combat dust pollution and ensure disposal of C&D waste.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Mega townships for middle income group
news.para: ​With huge response from the public over the venture developed at Navuluru in the capital region, the authority is now focusing on developing mega townships at Kesarapalli and three other locations surrounding the city.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's GB sets aside policy on building norms, sanction charges for slums
news.para: On February 26, TOI was the first to report that the civic body has made building plan sanction charges, guidelines of UDCPR and submission of five types of documents mandatory for construction or redevelopment, regularization of houses in notified slum areas.
